# define a function to create dummy variables for the remaing categorical variables
def create_dummy(data):
    cat_columns = data.select_dtypes(include='object').columns
    for col in cat_columns:
        dummy_cols = pd.get_dummies(data[col], prefix=col, drop_first = True)
        data = pd.concat([data, dummy_cols], axis = 1)
    return data

# Define a function to plot mean test and train scores with respect to alpha 
def draw_mean_test_train_plot(model_result):
    plt.plot(model_result['param_alpha'], model_result['mean_train_score'])
    plt.plot(model_result['param_alpha'], model_result['mean_test_score'])
    plt.xlabel('alpha')
    plt.ylabel('Negative Mean Absolute Error')
    plt.title("Negative Mean Absolute Error with respect to alpha")
    plt.legend(['Train score', 'Test score'], loc='upper right')
    plt.show()

# Define a function to plot for R2 score with respect to alpha value
def draw_r2_alpha(model_result):
    plt.plot(model_result['param_alpha'], model_result['mean_train_score'], label='Train Score')
    plt.plot(model_result['param_alpha'], model_result['mean_test_score'], label='Test Score')
    plt.xlabel('alpha')
    plt.ylabel('R2_score')
    plt.xscale('log')
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()

source.bfe5f99c: ### Problem Statement Surprise Housing, which is a US based company has decided to enter the Australian market. Data analytics is used by the company to purchase houses at a price below their actual values and flip them on at a higher price. The company has collected a data set for the same very purpose, from the sale of houses in Australia. The company is looking at prospective properties to buy to enter the market. You are required to build a regression model using regularisation in order to predict the actual value of the prospective properties and decide whether to invest in them or not. The company wants to know: - Which variables are significant in predicting the price of a house - How well those variables describe the price of a house Also, we need to determine the optimal value of lambda for ridge and lasso regression. ### Business Goal The requirement is to model the price of houses with the available independent variables. This model will then be used by the management to understand how exactly the prices vary with the variables. They can accordingly manipulate the strategy of the firm and concentrate on areas that will yield high returns. Further, the model will be a good way for management to understand the pricing dynamics of a new market.

# Conclusion : #### Following are the conclusion after performing regularization on the given dataset: - The Mean Squared Error observed when executing Ridge and Lasso regression are: - Ridge - 0.002012 - Lasso - 0.001858 So we observe that the Mean Squared Error of Lasso is lower than that of Ridge - The optimal value of lambda when executing Ridge and Lasso regression are: - Ridge - 2 - Lasso - 0.0001 - Following were the R-Squared value for train and test data set: - Ridge: - Train data set: 0.90 - Test data set: 0.89 - Lasso: - Train data set: 0.89 - Test data set: 0.90 - As we know that Lasso regression helps in feature reduction since the coefficient value of some feature equates to 0, hence Lasso has a better edge over Ridge.
So based on all these observations we would prefer Lasso regression in this case and the most significant predictors (taking top 30) affecting the sale price and having both positive and negative correlation are listed below along with their coefficients (marked in green color): - GrLivArea   0.242375 - OverallQual    0.192095 - GarageAre    0.076164 - OverallCond    0.076000 - BedroomAbvGr    0.067418 - Neighborhood_StoneBr    0.056899 - FullBath    0.050454 - BsmtQual    0.045655 - Neighborhood_NridgHt    0.041228 - BsmtFullBath    0.039956 - LotArea    0.037909 - SaleCondition_Alloca    0.036096 - Neighborhood_Crawfor    0.035528 - Neighborhood_NoRidge    0.034756 - Exterior1st_BrkFace    0.034276 - HalfBath    0.031754 - Neighborhood_IDOTRR    -0.031746 - Neighborhood_MeadowV    -0.031038 - BsmtExposure    0.029019 - BldgType_Twnhs    -0.028241 - MSSubClass    -0.024525 - KitchenQual    0.024159 - Fireplaces    0.023694 - RemodelOrConstructionAge    -0.023427 - Exterior1st_BrkComm    -0.022711 - Neighborhood_Veenker    0.021339 - MSZoning_FV    0.021300 - Neighborhood_Edwards    -0.021065 - Neighborhood_OldTown    -0.019411 - 2ndFlrSF    0.018000
